{
  "doc_id": "4019",
  "text": "Socio-demographic and behavioural characteristics are associated with delayed diagnosis or treatment, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] as well as adherence to treatment [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Among other factors, studies have associated age [CITATION_6] , gender [CITATION_7] , and alcohol consumption [CITATION_8] with access to therapy, but they have usually focused on single variables. The combined effect of several characteristics could be evaluated with a person-centred approach, which would begin by grouping persons with similar characteristics and then determining the associations between these groups and specific outcomes.",
